  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>A varied breakfast buffet is served in the dining room in the mornings. Tuck into pastries, breads and cakes with fruit, yogurt, cold cuts, cheese and hot options along with fresh coffee. </p>
<p>If you're on half board, you'll eat in the main restaurant. For dinner you'll have three courses with various choices.</p>
<p><strong>Grand Hotel Restaurant </strong>is where half board is taken. It has a great location on the edge of Lake Garda and offers Italian and international cuisine.</p>
<p><strong>Il Giardino dei Limoni</strong> has an <span>à</span> la carte menu that serves seasonal produce and has over 100 labels of wine. It's next to the pool so you can enjoy lake views if you have lunch or dinner here (payable locally).</p>
<p><strong>Pool Bar </strong>is open from 10am to 6pm during high season and offers drinks and light lunches between 12.30pm and 5pm.</p>
<p><strong>Piano Bar</strong> has live music most evenings and overlooks the lake. The bar staff make delicious cocktails - there's nothing quite like enjoying a Vesper Martini on the terrace and watching the sun set.</p>
<p>Early meals for children are available on request, 30 minutes before dinner service.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
