  <description><![CDATA[<p>Grand Hotel Gardone is a landmark hotel. It stretches out majestically along the lake and has been welcoming guests since 1884.</p>
<h2>An iconic hotel on Lake Garda</h2>
<p>In its time it's seen politicians, Hollywood stars and even royalty. You can learn a bit about its history as you walk down the halls – keep an eye out for pictures of the hotel back in it's hey-day. We love Winnie's bar which has live piano music most nights. It’s named after Winston Churchill who used to relax here with a cigar and a glass of Pol Roger. If you want to have a drink outside, the bar terrace is right on the lakefront and the perfect place to pull up a chair and order a drink.</p>
<h2>Plenty of summer activities on offer</h2>
<p>During the day, take a swim in the pool with fantastic lake views or head to the sunbathing terrace to top up your tan. When you want to explore, <a data-udi="umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11}" title="Gardone Riviera">Gardone</a>’s historic centre is right on the doorstep and Heller Botanical Gardens are close by. We love taking a stroll down the lakefront promenade straight from the hotel on a summer's day and you're right next to the ferry point so it's easy to visit other towns on Lake Garda.</p>]]></description>
